import React, {Fragment} from 'react'; import './paragraph.css'; import graduation from './graduation_friends.jpeg'; import sunset from './sunset_at_bahamas.jpeg'; import spanish from './learn_spanish.jpg'; import three_musk from './three_musk.jpeg'; import onitama from './onitama.jpeg'; import linkedin from './linkedin_icon.svg'; import git from './github_icon.png'; function Paragraph (props) { linkedin = () => { window.open('https://www.linkedin.com/in/jack-yang-85798122b/'); } if (props.topic === 'About me') { return (

About Me

Hi there, my name is Jack and I’m a 3rd year computer science specialist at UTM.

I completed my middle school and highschool in Vancouver and I came to Toronto 2

years ago for college. Personally I like Toronto better, just because the city

is bigger and has more places for exploration. Now that I’ve got used to Toronto’s

weather, it feels more like home than Vancouver and Suzhou, where my true hometown is.

In my spare time I also like learning Spanish and playing badminton. To me, learning a new

language means that I can get to know a culture that is completely new for someone of my

background. Up till now I can make some basic conversations in Spanish and if I’m suddenly

thrown off to Latin America, I won’t starve to death (LOL).

I also love traveling. This summer I went to the Bahamas, where I enjoyed the beach and

sunshine. Unlike Toronto, the sand on the beach there is incredibly soft, and the

water is always crystal clear. If you have never been before, it is a must-go (^_^).
